-- в”Ђв”Ђ Avo в”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђ
UPDATE tools SET
  short_description = COALESCE($q$Avo is a data governance and tracking-plan management platform that helps product, engineering, and data teams design, validate, and enforce clean analytics event schemas before they reach production.$q$, short_description),
  pricing_model = COALESCE($q$freemium$q$, pricing_model),
  starting_price = COALESCE($q$Free (2 editors); Team plan from $250/month billed annually$q$, starting_price),
  founded_year = COALESCE(2018, founded_year),
  company_size = COALESCE($q$Approximately 30-40 employees$q$, company_size),
  headquarters = COALESCE($q$Walnut, California, USA (with an office in Reykjavik, Iceland)$q$, headquarters),
  languages = ARRAY[$q$English$q$]::text[],
  seo_title = COALESCE($q$Avo Review 2026: Analytics Tracking Plan and Data Governance$q$, seo_title),
  seo_meta_description = COALESCE($q$Avo helps teams design and enforce clean analytics tracking plans. See Avo's features, pricing plans, and how it compares to spreadsheets in 2026.$q$, seo_meta_description),
  llm_readable_summary = COALESCE($q$Avo is a data governance and product-analytics tracking-plan management platform founded in 2018 by Stefania Olafsdottir (CEO), Solvi Logason, and Arni Hermann Reynisson, who previously worked together at the gaming company QuizUp. The company went through Y Combinator's Winter 2019 batch and has raised approximately 3.15 million dollars in total funding, including a 3 million dollar seed round in September 2020 led by GGV Capital with participation from Heavybit. Avo is headquartered in Walnut, California, with an additional office in Reykjavik, Iceland, and reports roughly 30 to 40 employees. The product replaces spreadsheet-based analytics tracking plans with a collaborative web interface where product managers, engineers, and data teams jointly define event and property schemas, naming conventions, and data types for product analytics. Its Codegen feature generates type-safe tracking libraries for iOS, Android, web, and backend languages so implementation matches the agreed schema, functioning like a compile-time spell-checker for analytics code. Its Inspector feature observes real production event data and flags discrepancies against the tracking plan, giving ongoing data-quality monitoring after launch, and its schema sync capability pushes validated schemas into downstream systems such as data warehouses or a company's own schema registry. Avo integrates with common analytics and customer data platforms including Segment, Amplitude, Mixpanel, Google Analytics, mParticle, and Rudderstack. Pricing follows a freemium model: a free plan includes two editor seats, unlimited comment-only seats, and a capped number of events observed by Inspector; a Team plan starts at 250 dollars per month billed annually (300 dollars billed monthly) for five editors, with additional editors priced at roughly 50 to 60 dollars per month each; and an Enterprise plan offers custom pricing with SSO, premium support, and enforceable governance policies. Avo's target audience is data-driven product and growth teams, typically at Series A through large enterprise companies, who rely on clean, trustworthy analytics data to make product decisions. It competes with general data governance and catalog tools as well as analytics-adjacent solutions like Segment Protocols and RudderStack Tracking Plans, differentiating itself through its dedicated, non-engineer-friendly tracking plan UI combined with developer-facing code generation and production-data inspection in one product.$q$, llm_readable_summary),
  status = 'published',
  noindex = false,
  sitemap_eligible = true,
  published_at = COALESCE(published_at, now()),
  updated_at = now()
WHERE id = 'f081d77d-6e8f-4442-9eac-bfe94b79c0c1';

