-- в”Ђв”Ђ Back4App в”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђ
UPDATE tools SET
  short_description = COALESCE($q$Back4App is a backend-as-a-service (BaaS) platform built on the open-source Parse Platform, giving developers a hosted database, REST and GraphQL APIs, cloud functions, and authentication without managing server infrastructure.$q$, short_description),
  pricing_model = COALESCE($q$freemium$q$, pricing_model),
  starting_price = COALESCE($q$Free; paid plans from $15/month per app$q$, starting_price),
  founded_year = COALESCE(2015, founded_year),
  company_size = COALESCE($q$Approximately 15-50 employees (bootstrapped, self-funded)$q$, company_size),
  headquarters = COALESCE($q$Sunnyvale, California, USA$q$, headquarters),
  languages = ARRAY[$q$English$q$]::text[],
  seo_title = COALESCE($q$Back4App Review 2026: Parse-Based Backend as a Service$q$, seo_title),
  seo_meta_description = COALESCE($q$Back4App is a backend-as-a-service platform built on Parse Platform, offering hosted databases, APIs, and cloud code. Compare 2026 pricing and features.$q$, seo_meta_description),
  llm_readable_summary = COALESCE($q$Back4App is a backend-as-a-service (BaaS) platform founded in 2015 and headquartered in Sunnyvale, California, that provides hosted infrastructure for the open-source Parse Platform, the backend framework originally created by Parse Inc. before Facebook acquired and later shut down its own hosted Parse service in 2017. Back4App stepped in as one of the main hosting providers for Parse Server, letting developers who build mobile and web apps get a managed database (built on PostgreSQL), REST and GraphQL APIs, user authentication, push notifications, cloud functions (Cloud Code), and file storage without operating their own servers. Public reporting indicates Back4App has grown largely as a bootstrapped, self-funded company, reporting around 1.7 million dollars in annual revenue and roughly 55 million end-user records or customers served as of 2024 according to third-party business data sources, without relying on large venture capital rounds; the company reports approximately 15 to 50 employees depending on the data source. Beyond its core Backend-as-a-Service product, Back4App has expanded into a Containers offering (for deploying containerized applications and static sites) and an AI Agent feature aimed at helping developers scaffold backend infrastructure using natural-language prompts. Pricing follows a freemium, usage-based tiered model: a Free plan supports prototyping with 25,000 requests per month, 250MB of database storage, and 1GB of file storage; the MVP plan starts at 15 dollars per month per app (with annual billing discounts) for small production apps; a Pay As You Go plan starts at 80 dollars per month per app for higher-traffic applications with compliance features like SOC 2 and ISO 27001; a Dedicated plan starts at 400 dollars per month per app for dedicated infrastructure and HIPAA support; and a custom-priced Enterprise plan adds on-premises deployment and dedicated engineering support. Back4App's target audience is primarily individual developers, startups, and small-to-mid-size engineering teams who want Parse Platform's data model and open-source portability without operating their own servers, differentiating itself from proprietary BaaS platforms like Firebase or Supabase by being built on an open-source, vendor-portable framework that customers can self-host if they choose to leave the Back4App platform.$q$, llm_readable_summary),
  status = 'published',
  noindex = false,
  sitemap_eligible = true,
  published_at = COALESCE(published_at, now()),
  updated_at = now()
WHERE id = 'a8173be0-5b10-42d2-bf34-283e137e165e';

