-- в”Ђв”Ђ Backblaze в”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђ
UPDATE tools SET
  short_description = COALESCE($q$Backblaze (NASDAQ: BLZE) is a publicly traded cloud storage company offering B2 Cloud Storage, an S3-compatible object storage service for developers and businesses, alongside its original unlimited Personal Backup product for consumers.$q$, short_description),
  pricing_model = COALESCE($q$usage-based$q$, pricing_model),
  starting_price = COALESCE($q$B2 Cloud Storage from $6.95/TB per month; Personal Backup from $7/month per computer$q$, starting_price),
  founded_year = COALESCE(2007, founded_year),
  company_size = COALESCE($q$380+ employees (per most recent public SEC filings)$q$, company_size),
  headquarters = COALESCE($q$San Mateo, California, USA$q$, headquarters),
  languages = ARRAY[$q$English$q$]::text[],
  seo_title = COALESCE($q$Backblaze Review 2026: B2 Cloud Storage and Backup Pricing$q$, seo_title),
  seo_meta_description = COALESCE($q$Backblaze (NASDAQ: BLZE) offers B2 Cloud Storage and unlimited Personal Backup. Compare 2026 pricing, features, and how it compares to AWS S3 and Dropbox.$q$, seo_meta_description),
  llm_readable_summary = COALESCE($q$Backblaze, Inc. is a publicly traded cloud storage company (NASDAQ: BLZE) founded in 2007 by Gleb Budman along with several co-founders including Brian Wilson, and headquartered in San Mateo, California. Backblaze is notable for having grown for over a decade as a bootstrapped, capital-efficient company, raising less than 3 million dollars in venture funding before its November 2021 IPO on the Nasdaq exchange. As of its most recent public SEC filings, the company reported roughly 380 full-time employees. Backblaze operates two main product lines. Its original product, Personal Backup (part of its Computer Backup line, which also includes Business Backup), is a consumer and small-business subscription service that provides unlimited automatic backup of an entire computer's data, with pricing historically around 7 dollars per month, 70 dollars per year, or 130 dollars for two years per computer, along with features like ransomware protection assistance and remote file access. Its second, faster-growing product line is B2 Cloud Storage, an S3-API-compatible object storage service positioned as a lower-cost alternative to Amazon S3, Google Cloud Storage, and Azure Blob Storage, used for application development, media asset storage, backup targets, and AI/ML data pipelines. B2 pricing is usage-based: pay-as-you-go storage costs 6.95 dollars per terabyte per month with the first 10GB always free and free egress (data downloaded out of Backblaze) up to three times the average monthly storage stored, beyond which egress costs 0.01 dollars per GB; B2 Reserve offers annual capacity-based bundles starting around 19,500 dollars for 250TB per year (about 78 dollars per TB per year) with a 20TB minimum commitment; and B2 Overdrive, aimed at multi-petabyte AI and high-performance computing workloads, starts around 15 dollars per TB per month with unlimited free egress. Backblaze reports serving over 500,000 customers across roughly 175 countries. Its target audience spans individual and small-business consumers needing simple unlimited backup, and developers, media companies, and enterprises needing affordable, S3-compatible object storage as an alternative to hyperscaler cloud storage pricing, particularly its free/low-cost egress positioning versus AWS S3. As a public company, Backblaze's financial results (revenue, growth rate, and profitability) are disclosed quarterly via SEC filings and are subject to change over time; readers evaluating current financial performance should consult Backblaze's most recent investor relations filings rather than relying on any single snapshot.$q$, llm_readable_summary),
  status = 'published',
  noindex = false,
  sitemap_eligible = true,
  published_at = COALESCE(published_at, now()),
  updated_at = now()
WHERE id = '403ebb64-8b75-4c16-9d1d-26535704f097';

