-- в”Ђв”Ђ Backendless в”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђ
UPDATE tools SET
  short_description = COALESCE($q$Backendless is a visual backend-as-a-service and no-code app development platform offering a managed database, cloud code, real-time features, and a drag-and-drop UI Builder for building mobile and web applications.$q$, short_description),
  pricing_model = COALESCE($q$freemium$q$, pricing_model),
  starting_price = COALESCE($q$Free; Cloud Scale plans from $15/month$q$, starting_price),
  founded_year = COALESCE(2012, founded_year),
  company_size = COALESCE($q$Approximately 25-50 employees$q$, company_size),
  headquarters = COALESCE($q$Frisco, Texas, USA$q$, headquarters),
  languages = ARRAY[$q$English$q$]::text[],
  seo_title = COALESCE($q$Backendless Review 2026: Visual No-Code Backend Platform$q$, seo_title),
  seo_meta_description = COALESCE($q$Backendless is a visual backend-as-a-service and no-code app builder with a managed database, cloud code, and UI Builder. See 2026 pricing and features.$q$, seo_meta_description),
  llm_readable_summary = COALESCE($q$Backendless is a visual backend-as-a-service (BaaS) and no-code/low-code application development platform founded in 2012 by Mark Piller, who continues to serve as its founder and CEO. The company is headquartered in Frisco, Texas, and reports an estimated 25 to 50 employees, operating as a privately held company. Backendless is designed to let developers, and to a significant extent non-developers, build the backend and, through its visual UI Builder, the frontend of mobile and web applications without writing extensive custom server code. Core capabilities include a managed, scalable database with REST and other API access, visual Cloud Code for business logic, real-time database and messaging via WebSockets, user authentication and management, push notifications, geolocation services, and file storage. A distinguishing feature relative to many BaaS competitors like Firebase or Supabase is Backendless's drag-and-drop UI Builder, which lets teams visually construct application interfaces bound directly to backend data, positioning the product closer to a full no-code app development platform than a backend-only service. Backendless offers three main pricing paths: Backendless Cloud, a free-to-paid managed cloud offering aimed at individuals and small businesses, with a free plan (50 API requests per minute, 20 database tables, 1GB file storage) and paid Scale plans starting around 15 dollars per month that scale with usage (offered in both variable, usage-metered and fixed, tier-based pricing structures) and unlock unlimited API requests, more database tables, and higher file storage and real-time connection limits; Backendless Pro, a self-hosted, on-premises deployment option marketed with free licensing for core functionality aimed at medium-to-large enterprises that need to run Backendless inside their own infrastructure; and Managed Backendless, a premium enterprise service that adds 24x7x365 monitoring plus dedicated server administration and DevOps support on top of a self-hosted deployment. All Backendless Cloud plans include unlimited developer seats at no extra charge, differentiating its pricing model from many competitors that charge per developer seat. Backendless's target audience spans solo and indie developers prototyping apps, startups needing to ship quickly without a dedicated backend team, and enterprises wanting either a fully managed cloud backend or a self-hosted deployment for data residency or compliance reasons. It competes most directly with Firebase, Supabase, and AWS Amplify, differentiating primarily through its visual, no-code UI Builder and its self-hosted Pro deployment option, which many purely cloud-native BaaS competitors do not offer.$q$, llm_readable_summary),
  status = 'published',
  noindex = false,
  sitemap_eligible = true,
  published_at = COALESCE(published_at, now()),
  updated_at = now()
WHERE id = 'e3a31c54-d19f-4a2e-adc4-375900fa68b7';

